[[File:Vista interior edificio Parque Cultural Valparaíso.JPG|thumb|upright|The "Broadcasting Building" of the [[Parque Cultural de Valparaíso]] (PCdV) which has been established on a former prison's ground on Cerro Cárcel.<ref>[http://pcdv.cl/web/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/RESE%C3%91A-traducido.pdf ''PCdV – Historical Review'']. pcdv.cl</ref><ref>Michael Webb: [http://www.architectural-review.com/buildings/open-city-ex-crcel-parque-cultural-by-hlps-in-valparaso-chile/8637480.article# ''Open City: Ex Cárcel Parque Cultural by HLPS in Valparaíso, Chile'']. 10/24/2012 architectural-review.com</ref>]]

'''Cárcel Hill''' (''Cerro Cárcel'') is one of the [[Hills of Valparaíso|42 hills]] of [[Valparaíso]], [[Chile]]. It is the site of the city's old infamous [[prison]], which has now been turned into an urban [[cultural center]].

